<CONTENT id="_4046455_1"><TITLE value="Introduction"/><TITLECOLOR value="#000000"/><DESCRIPTION
   value=""/><BODY><TEXT>&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;img src="@X@EmbeddedFile.requestUrlStub@X@bbcswebdav/xid-51963817_1" alt="" width="802" height="285" style="border: 0px solid #000000;"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&#xd;
&lt;p&gt;Thanks for choosing North Metropolitan TAFE as your training provider.&lt;/p&gt;&#xd;
&lt;p&gt;You can use the menu on the left to navigate through this unit.&lt;/p&gt;&#xd;
&lt;ul&gt;&#xd;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Learning Materials&lt;/strong&gt; - In this&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;section you will find all of the learning resources required for this unit.&lt;/li&gt;&#xd;
&lt;li&gt;You will find details of all of the assessments in the &lt;strong&gt;Assessment&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;section&lt;/li&gt;&#xd;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;My Grades &lt;/strong&gt;is where you will find your assessment feedback once marked&lt;/li&gt;&#xd;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Blackboard Collaborate&lt;/strong&gt; is an online Classroom where your lecturer may choose to meet or hold sessions&lt;/li&gt;&#xd;
&lt;li&gt;In the &lt;strong&gt;Communication&lt;/strong&gt; section you will find tools to contact your lecturer or classmates&lt;/li&gt;&#xd;
&lt;li&gt;If you have any questions or problems, please see the &lt;strong&gt;Staff contacts&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;section&lt;/li&gt;&#xd;
&lt;/ul&gt;&#xd;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xd;
&lt;p&gt;This unit describes the performance outcome, knowledge and skills required to recognise threats, risks and vulnerabilities to cyber security in an organisation.&lt;/p&gt;&#xd;
&lt;p&gt;The threats to an organisation include networks, machines, applications, data, users and infrastructure.&lt;/p&gt;&#xd;
&lt;p&gt;In your study, you will investigate common cyber security attack mechanisms and an introduction to threat management as well as security issues surrounding Internet of Things (IoT) devices.&lt;/p&gt;&#xd;
&lt;p&gt;You will also investigate the implementation of tools and systems an organisation can use for protection against cyber-attacks.&lt;/p&gt;</TEXT><TYPE
